    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "41b2a84f_5cd40fb5",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/deriver/derive_invocation.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 79,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-30T19:50:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tried removing the client from the context, but there\u0027s an issue:\n\nTests want to provide their own http client, currently doing this by setting it in the context, I couldn\u0027t think of a way of removing it from the context without changing the signature of the api.\n\nThen I tried moving the functions to inject the client into the context and (getting it out of) into this module, but the issue there is that internal/services/deriver/chromium needs to get the client from the context, and cannot import deriver due to cyclic imports. Instead, I moved the http client related functions into their own file under internal, PTAL.\n\nI think moving the code from this http-client-specific file in the internal module into deriver as you suggested is possible, but would need to do some piping in the deriver/chromium module. So how about I do that in a follow up change?",
      "parentUuid": "48ba7777_119031c5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 79,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 79,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "ef52b90e8bbe18f5f26171f94b16b0b5d235233a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "83b132ac_79f1a438",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/services/deriver/derive_invocation.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 79,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-31T07:26:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "in the past, there was no \"deriver\" package, so the \"chromium\" package used to make sense. Now both deriver and chromium packages are chromium-specific and little sense to have them separated. When packages are very co-related, cyclic dependencies start to happen. \n\nCombining the packages would be busy work in deprecated codebase, so I don\u0027t recommend that, but we could move this context+client code to chromium package. Then there would be no cycle dep. This or another CL is fine.",
      "parentUuid": "41b2a84f_5cd40fb5",
      "range": {
